This paper is about active learning for object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses self-learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) to analyze text data, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses security and privacy concerns related to object detection, which could fall under cryptography (cs.CR).
